  "title": "Lines: Slope, Equations & Distance",
  "content": "<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\">The Coordinate Plane</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">Every point on the coordinate plane is written as <strong>(x, y)</strong>:<br><br>\n<ul style=\"margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem;\">\n<li style=\"margin: 0.4rem 0;\">The <em>x-value</em> tells you how far left or right from the origin</li>\n<li style=\"margin: 0.4rem 0;\">The <em>y-value</em> tells you how far up or down</li>\n</ul></p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"400\" height=\"400\" viewBox=\"-10 -10 420 420\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"background: white; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\">\n  <defs>\n    <pattern id=\"grid\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" patternUnits=\"userSpaceOnUse\">\n      <path d=\"M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/>\n    </pattern>\n  </defs>\n  <rect width=\"400\" height=\"400\" fill=\"url(#grid)\"/>\n  <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"200\" x2=\"400\" y2=\"200\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <line x1=\"200\" y1=\"0\" x2=\"200\" y2=\"400\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <text x=\"390\" y=\"190\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#000\">x</text>\n  <text x=\"210\" y=\"15\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#000\">y</text>\n  <line x1=\"240\" y1=\"195\" x2=\"240\" y2=\"205\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>\n  <text x=\"240\" y=\"220\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#666\" text-anchor=\"middle\">1</text>\n  <line x1=\"280\" y1=\"195\" x2=\"280\" y2=\"205\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>\n  <text x=\"280\" y=\"220\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#666\" text-anchor=\"middle\">2</text>\n  <line x1=\"160\" y1=\"195\" x2=\"160\" y2=\"205\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>\n  <text x=\"160\" y=\"220\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#666\" text-anchor=\"middle\">âˆ’1</text>\n  <line x1=\"120\" y1=\"195\" x2=\"120\" y2=\"205\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>\n  <text x=\"120\" y=\"220\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#666\" text-anchor=\"middle\">âˆ’2</text>\n  <line x1=\"195\" y1=\"160\" x2=\"205\" y2=\"160\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>\n  <text x=\"185\" y=\"165\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#666\" text-anchor=\"end\">1</text>\n  <line x1=\"195\" y1=\"120\" x2=\"205\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>\n  <text x=\"185\" y=\"125\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#666\" text-anchor=\"end\">2</text>\n  <line x1=\"195\" y1=\"240\" x2=\"205\" y2=\"240\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>\n  <text x=\"185\" y=\"245\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#666\" text-anchor=\"end\">âˆ’1</text>\n  <line x1=\"195\" y1=\"280\" x2=\"205\" y2=\"280\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>\n  <text x=\"185\" y=\"285\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#666\" text-anchor=\"end\">âˆ’2</text>\n  <circle cx=\"280\" cy=\"120\" r=\"5\" fill=\"#2563eb\"/>\n  <text x=\"300\" y=\"115\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#2563eb\" font-weight=\"bold\">(2, 2)</text>\n</svg>\n</div></div>\n\n<ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">ğŸ’¡ Key Idea:</span></li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">The origin (0, 0) is where the x-axis and y-axis meet. Positive x is right, negative x is left. Positive y is up, negative y is down!</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\">What is <strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Slope</strong></strong>?</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">Slope measures how <strong>steep</strong> a line is. It tells you how much y changes when x increases by 1.</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Slope Formula</h4>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.1rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  m = <span style=\"font-size: 1.3rem;\">(yâ‚‚ âˆ’ yâ‚) / (xâ‚‚ âˆ’ xâ‚)</span>\n</p>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>In words:</strong> slope = rise / run = change in y / change in x</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Types of Slope</h4>\n\n<table style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; font-size: 0.9rem;\">\n  <tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;\">\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.85rem;\">Type</th>\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.85rem;\">Slope Value</th>\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.85rem;\">Visual</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Positive</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">m > 0</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">Line goes up as you move right â†—</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Negative</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">m < 0</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">Line goes down as you move right â†˜</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Zero</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">m = 0</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">Horizontal line â†’</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Undefined</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">m = undefined</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">Vertical line â†‘</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n\n<div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;\">\n  <div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"450\" height=\"450\" viewBox=\"-10 -10 470 470\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"background: white; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\">\n  <defs>\n    <pattern id=\"grid-slope\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" patternUnits=\"userSpaceOnUse\">\n      <path d=\"M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/>\n    </pattern>\n    <marker id=\"arrowRed\" markerWidth=\"8\" markerHeight=\"8\" refX=\"7\" refY=\"4\" orient=\"auto\">\n      <path d=\"M0,0 L0,8 L8,4 z\" fill=\"#ef4444\"/>\n    </marker>\n    <marker id=\"arrowGreen\" markerWidth=\"8\" markerHeight=\"8\" refX=\"4\" refY=\"0\" orient=\"auto\">\n      <path d=\"M0,0 L8,0 L4,8 z\" fill=\"#10b981\"/>\n    </marker>\n  </defs>\n  <rect width=\"450\" height=\"450\" fill=\"url(#grid-slope)\"/>\n  <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"225\" x2=\"450\" y2=\"225\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <line x1=\"225\" y1=\"0\" x2=\"225\" y2=\"450\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <line x1=\"100\" y1=\"325\" x2=\"350\" y2=\"75\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <circle cx=\"165\" cy=\"265\" r=\"5\" fill=\"#2563eb\"/>\n  <text x=\"145\" y=\"285\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#2563eb\">(âˆ’1, âˆ’1)</text>\n  <circle cx=\"285\" cy=\"145\" r=\"5\" fill=\"#2563eb\"/>\n  <text x=\"295\" y=\"140\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#2563eb\">(2, 2)</text>\n  <line x1=\"165\" y1=\"265\" x2=\"280\" y2=\"265\" stroke=\"#ef4444\" stroke-width=\"2\" marker-end=\"url(#arrowRed)\"/>\n  <text x=\"220\" y=\"255\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#ef4444\" font-weight=\"bold\">run = 3</text>\n  <line x1=\"285\" y1=\"265\" x2=\"285\" y2=\"150\" stroke=\"#10b981\" stroke-width=\"2\" marker-end=\"url(#arrowGreen)\"/>\n  <text x=\"295\" y=\"210\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#10b981\" font-weight=\"bold\">rise = 3</text>\n  <text x=\"225\" y=\"430\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#000\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-weight=\"bold\">slope = rise Ã· run = 3 Ã· 3 = 1</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n  <div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"400\" height=\"420\" viewBox=\"-10 -10 420 440\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"background: white; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\">\n  <defs>\n    <pattern id=\"grid-si\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" patternUnits=\"userSpaceOnUse\">\n      <path d=\"M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/>\n    </pattern>\n  </defs>\n  <rect width=\"400\" height=\"400\" fill=\"url(#grid-si)\"/>\n  <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"200\" x2=\"400\" y2=\"200\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <line x1=\"200\" y1=\"0\" x2=\"200\" y2=\"400\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <line x1=\"60\" y1=\"320\" x2=\"300\" y2=\"40\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <circle cx=\"200\" cy=\"160\" r=\"6\" fill=\"#ef4444\"/>\n  <text x=\"215\" y=\"155\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#ef4444\" font-weight=\"bold\">b = 1</text>\n  <text x=\"215\" y=\"175\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#666\">(y-intercept)</text>\n  <text x=\"200\" y=\"430\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"20\" fill=\"#2563eb\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-weight=\"bold\">y = 2x + 1</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\">Slope-Intercept Form</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">The most common form of a line equation is <strong>slope-intercept form</strong>:</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.2rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 2px solid #10b981; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>y = mx + b</strong>\n</p>\n\n<ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>m</strong> = slope (steepness of the line)</li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>b</strong> = <strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">y-intercept</strong></strong> (where line crosses y-axis)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">ğŸ’¡ ACT Tip:</span></li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">If you see y = mx + b, you can immediately identify the slope (m) and y-intercept (b) without any calculation!</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 1</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> What is the slope and y-intercept of y = 3x âˆ’ 2?</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong> Compare to y = mx + b<br>\n  Slope m = 3<br>\n  Y-intercept b = âˆ’2\n</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\">Point-Slope Form</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">When you know a point (xâ‚, yâ‚) and the slope m, use <strong>point-slope form</strong>:</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.1rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  y âˆ’ yâ‚ = m(x âˆ’ xâ‚)\n</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 2</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> Write the equation of a line with slope 2 passing through point (1, 3).</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong><br>\n  Use point-slope: y âˆ’ yâ‚ = m(x âˆ’ xâ‚)<br>\n  Plug in m = 2, (xâ‚, yâ‚) = (1, 3):<br>\n  y âˆ’ 3 = 2(x âˆ’ 1)<br>\n  y âˆ’ 3 = 2x âˆ’ 2<br>\n  y = 2x + 1\n</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\">Standard Form</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">Some line equations appear in <strong>standard form</strong>:</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.1rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  Ax + By = C\n</p>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">To find slope from standard form: m = âˆ’A/B</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Parallel</strong></strong> & <strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Perpendicular</strong></strong> Lines</h3>\n\n<table style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; font-size: 0.9rem;\">\n  <tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;\">\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.85rem;\">Type</th>\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.85rem;\">Slope Relationship</th>\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.85rem;\">Example</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Parallel</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Same slope (mâ‚ = mâ‚‚)</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">m = 2 and m = 2</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Perpendicular</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Negative reciprocals (mâ‚ Ã— mâ‚‚ = âˆ’1)</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">m = 2 and m = âˆ’Â½</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n\n\n  <p style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: #92400e; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">âš ï¸ Common Mistake:</p>\n  <p style=\"font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5; color: #78350f; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">Perpendicular lines have slopes that multiply to âˆ’1, NOT slopes that add to 0!</p>\n\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Midpoint</strong></strong> Formula</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">To find the <strong>midpoint</strong> between two points (xâ‚, yâ‚) and (xâ‚‚, yâ‚‚):</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.1rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  Midpoint = (<span style=\"font-size: 1.2rem;\">(xâ‚ + xâ‚‚)/2, (yâ‚ + yâ‚‚)/2</span>)\n</p>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>In words:</strong> Average the x-coordinates, average the y-coordinates!</p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"400\" height=\"420\" viewBox=\"-10 -10 420 440\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"background: white; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\">\n  <defs>\n    <pattern id=\"grid-dist\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" patternUnits=\"userSpaceOnUse\">\n      <path d=\"M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/>\n    </pattern>\n  </defs>\n  <rect width=\"400\" height=\"400\" fill=\"url(#grid-dist)\"/>\n  <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"200\" x2=\"400\" y2=\"200\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <line x1=\"200\" y1=\"0\" x2=\"200\" y2=\"400\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <circle cx=\"160\" cy=\"280\" r=\"5\" fill=\"#2563eb\"/>\n  <text x=\"140\" y=\"300\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#2563eb\">(1, âˆ’2)</text>\n  <circle cx=\"320\" cy=\"120\" r=\"5\" fill=\"#2563eb\"/>\n  <text x=\"325\" y=\"115\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#2563eb\">(4, 2)</text>\n  <line x1=\"160\" y1=\"280\" x2=\"320\" y2=\"280\" stroke=\"#ef4444\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,5\"/>\n  <line x1=\"320\" y1=\"280\" x2=\"320\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"#10b981\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"5,5\"/>\n  <line x1=\"160\" y1=\"280\" x2=\"320\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <text x=\"240\" y=\"270\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#ef4444\">Î”x = 3</text>\n  <text x=\"330\" y=\"200\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#10b981\">Î”y = 4</text>\n  <text x=\"220\" y=\"190\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#2563eb\" font-weight=\"bold\">d = 5</text>\n  <text x=\"200\" y=\"430\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#000\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-weight=\"bold\">d = âˆš(3Â² + 4Â²) = âˆš25 = 5</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 3</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> Find the midpoint between (1, âˆ’2) and (4, 3).</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong><br>\n  Midpoint = ((1+4)/2, (âˆ’2+3)/2)<br>\n  Midpoint = (5/2, 1/2)<br>\n  Midpoint = (2.5, 0.5)\n</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Distance</strong></strong> Formula</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">To find the <strong>distance</strong> between two points (xâ‚, yâ‚) and (xâ‚‚, yâ‚‚):</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.1rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  d = <span style=\"font-size: 1.3rem;\">âˆš[(xâ‚‚ âˆ’ xâ‚)Â² + (yâ‚‚ âˆ’ yâ‚)Â²]</span>\n</p>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>This is just the Pythagorean theorem!</strong> Think of it as finding the hypotenuse of a right triangle.</p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"550\" height=\"300\" viewBox=\"0 0 550 300\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"background: white; max-width: 100%; height: auto;\">\n  <!-- Parallel section -->\n  <text x=\"135\" y=\"30\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"20\" fill=\"#000\" font-weight=\"bold\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Parallel Lines</text>\n  <line x1=\"30\" y1=\"80\" x2=\"240\" y2=\"160\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <line x1=\"30\" y1=\"140\" x2=\"240\" y2=\"220\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <text x=\"135\" y=\"250\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#2563eb\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-weight=\"bold\">Same slope: mâ‚ = mâ‚‚</text>\n  <!-- Perpendicular section -->\n  <text x=\"410\" y=\"30\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"20\" fill=\"#000\" font-weight=\"bold\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Perpendicular Lines</text>\n  <line x1=\"310\" y1=\"150\" x2=\"510\" y2=\"150\" stroke=\"#ef4444\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <line x1=\"410\" y1=\"70\" x2=\"410\" y2=\"230\" stroke=\"#10b981\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <rect x=\"398\" y=\"138\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/>\n  <text x=\"410\" y=\"260\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#2563eb\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-weight=\"bold\">mâ‚ Ã— mâ‚‚ = âˆ’1</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 4</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> Find the distance between (1, 0) and (5, 3).</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong><br>\n  d = âˆš[(5âˆ’1)Â² + (3âˆ’0)Â²]<br>\n  d = âˆš[4Â² + 3Â²]<br>\n  d = âˆš[16 + 9]<br>\n  d = âˆš25<br>\n  d = 5\n</p>\n\n\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">âœ“ Key Formulas Summary</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Slope:</strong> m = (yâ‚‚ âˆ’ yâ‚)/(xâ‚‚ âˆ’ xâ‚)</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Slope-Intercept:</strong> y = mx + b</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Point-Slope:</strong> y âˆ’ yâ‚ = m(x âˆ’ xâ‚)</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Parallel Lines:</strong> Same slope</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Perpendicular Lines:</strong> mâ‚ Ã— mâ‚‚ = âˆ’1</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Midpoint:</strong> ((xâ‚+xâ‚‚)/2, (yâ‚+yâ‚‚)/2)</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Distance:</strong> âˆš[(xâ‚‚âˆ’xâ‚)Â² + (yâ‚‚âˆ’yâ‚)Â²]</li>\n  </ul>\n\n\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">âœ“ Key Takeaways</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Slope = rise/run = (yâ‚‚âˆ’yâ‚)/(xâ‚‚âˆ’xâ‚)</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Slope-intercept form: y = mx + b</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Parallel lines have equal slopes</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Perpendicular lines have negative reciprocal slopes</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Midpoint = ((xâ‚+xâ‚‚)/2, (yâ‚+yâ‚‚)/2)</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Distance = âˆš[(xâ‚‚âˆ’xâ‚)Â² + (yâ‚‚âˆ’yâ‚)Â²]</strong></li>\n  </ul>\n\n\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">âœ“ Key Takeaways</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Slope = rise/run = (yâ‚‚âˆ’yâ‚)/(xâ‚‚âˆ’xâ‚)</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Slope-intercept form: y = mx + b</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Parallel lines have equal slopes</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Perpendicular lines have negative reciprocal slopes</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Midpoint = ((xâ‚+xâ‚‚)/2, (yâ‚+yâ‚‚)/2)</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Distance = âˆš[(xâ‚‚âˆ’xâ‚)Â² + (yâ‚‚âˆ’yâ‚)Â²]</strong></li>\n  </ul>\n\n<div style=\"background: #f0fdf4; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; margin: 3rem 0 2rem 0; border-left: 4px solid #10b981;\">\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">âœ“ Key Takeaways</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Slope = rise/run = (yâ‚‚âˆ’yâ‚)/(xâ‚‚âˆ’xâ‚)</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Slope-intercept form: y = mx + b</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Parallel lines have equal slopes</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Perpendicular lines have negative reciprocal slopes</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Midpoint = ((xâ‚+xâ‚‚)/2, (yâ‚+yâ‚‚)/2)</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Distance = âˆš[(xâ‚‚âˆ’xâ‚)Â² + (yâ‚‚âˆ’yâ‚)Â²]</strong></li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
